{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Lz8aNK27k83g9vN417rNgn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is healthy. Here's a summary of what was wrong and what was fixed:\n\n**Root cause:** `app-user` had `write` and `read` permissions on the `/app` vhost but was missing the `configure` permission. Declaring (creating) a queue via the RabbitMQ management API requires configure permission — without it, the PUT request to `/api/queues/%2Fapp/app-queue` returned `Access refused`.\n\n**Fix:** Ran `rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` to grant full configure+write+read on `/app`.\n\n**Current state:**\n- `app-producer` — `1/1 Running`, publishing messages every 2s\n- `/app` vhost — `app-queue` is type `classic` with 29 messages (and growing)\n- RabbitMQ cluster — all 3 nodes healthy (`rabbitmq-0/1/2` all `Running`)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":351,"cache_read_input_tokens":33086,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":351},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"50959385-3984-4747-974c-feecb33511e1","uuid":"f31fc876-f955-453d-a643-e63b71b3fcb6","request_id":"req_011CcLEt17ur4S6mR83U9TpT"}
